Mongo:
 
**replicating tables between database instances:**

db.xlat.find().forEach(function(d){ db.getSiblingDB('test')['xlat'].insert(d); });

**Update string value to int value:**

db.waves.find().forEach(function(data) {
    db.waves.update({_id:data._id},{$set:{stddev:parseInt(data.stddev)}});
})


** insert into sample_group: **
db.sample_groups.insert({"project":"Aortic Stenosis_Priest Study_PBMCs", "default":"sample_group", "available":["sample_label","sample_group","age","sex","sentrix_id"]})



**Upgrade Pyjade.**
	sudo pip install pyjade --upgrade

*** getting a list of genes or exons ***

ensembl.org/biomart:  
* Parameters:
Homo sapiens genes (GRCh37.p12)
* Filters
[None selected]
* Attributes
Ensembl Gene ID
Ensembl Transcript ID
Exon Chr Start (bp)
Exon Chr End (bp)
Constitutive Exon
Exon Rank in Transcript
cDNA coding start
cDNA coding end
Genomic coding start
Genomic coding end
Ensembl Exon ID
Ensembl Protein ID
Chromosome Name
Gene Start (bp)
Gene End (bp)
Transcript Start (bp)
Transcript End (bp)
Strand
Associated Gene Name
5‘ UTR Start
5‘ UTR End
3‘ UTR End
3‘ UTR Start
Description
Transcript count
CDS Length
Gene Biotype
CDS Start
CDS End


Export:
mongoexport --db human_epigenetics --collection annotations > ~/Data/Pavlab/annotations.json

Import
mongoimport --db human_epigenetics --collection annotations --file annotations.json

set up remote server (trial site...):
 ssh -l <name> -p 22000 -D 9999 <server>
